Class Directive

java.lang.Object
  Directive

public class Directive
extends java.lang.Object

Author:
Kermit Stearns. This class is an object that allows us to store a Directive and determine certain attributes of that Directive such as codeLocation, directive name, label type, operand types as well as separating the operands for directives with operands.
